content-flag-management.explanation:
# Content Flag Management - SDK v5.11.0+

Content moderation via flags and comments. Moderators can flag content for review,
take action on flags (delete content, ban users), and manage pool comments.

## Content Types

Flags can be created for:
- `MESSAGE` - Chat messages
- `COMMENT` - Pool comments
- `STREAM` - Live streams (admin only)

## Creating Content Flags

```typescript
import { createLaunchpadSDK, CONTENT_TYPE } from '@gala-chain/launchpad-sdk';

const sdk = createLaunchpadSDK({
  privateKey: process.env.PRIVATE_KEY,
});

await sdk.login();

// Flag a chat message
const flag = await sdk.createFlag({
  tokenName: 'mytoken',
  contentType: CONTENT_TYPE.MESSAGE,
  contentId: 'msg-123',
  reason: 'Spam/harassment',
});

```

## Listing Flags

```typescript
// List all pending flags for a token
const flags = await sdk.listFlags({
  tokenName: 'mytoken',
  status: 'PENDING',
  page: 1,
  limit: 20,
});

for (const flag of flags.flags) {

}
```

## Taking Action on Flags

```typescript
// Dismiss a flag (no action taken)
await sdk.dismissFlag(flagId);

// Take action - delete content only
await sdk.actionFlag(flagId, {
  action: 'DELETE_CONTENT',
});

// Take action - ban the user
await sdk.actionFlag(flagId, {
  action: 'BAN_USER',
  banDuration: 3600, // 1 hour ban
});

// Take action - delete content AND ban user
await sdk.actionFlag(flagId, {
  action: 'DELETE_AND_BAN',
  banDuration: 86400, // 24 hour ban
});
```

## Managing Pool Comments with Reactions

Comments include a `messageId` for reactions integration and optional `reactions` data.

```typescript
// Fetch comments for a pool (with reactions data)
const comments = await sdk.getComments({
  tokenName: 'mytoken',
  page: 1,
  limit: 20,
});

for (const comment of comments.comments) {

  // Check reactions on this comment
  if (comment.reactions) {

    for (const reaction of comment.reactions.reactions) {

    }
  }
}

// Post a comment (requires JWT auth)
await sdk.login();
const newComment = await sdk.createComment({
  tokenName: 'mytoken',
  content: 'Great project! Looking forward to the launch.',
});

// Add a reaction to a comment using its messageId
await sdk.addReaction({
  messageId: newComment.comment.messageId,
  reaction: '👍',
});

// Remove a reaction
await sdk.removeReaction({
  messageId: newComment.comment.messageId,
  reaction: '👍',
});

// Delete a comment (moderator only)
await sdk.deleteComment({ commentId: comment.id });
```

## SDK Methods Reference

| Method | Description | Auth |
|--------|-------------|------|
| `createFlag(options)` | Flag content for review | JWT |
| `listFlags(options)` | List flags for a token | API key OR JWT (Moderator) |
| `dismissFlag(flagId)` | Dismiss flag (no action) | API key OR JWT (Moderator) |
| `actionFlag(flagId, options)` | Take action on flag | API key OR JWT (Moderator) |
| `getComments(options)` | Get pool comments with reactions | None (public) |
| `createComment(options)` | Post a comment, returns messageId | JWT |
| `deleteComment(options)` | Delete a comment | API key OR JWT (Moderator) |
| `addReaction(options)` | Add reaction to comment/message | JWT |
| `removeReaction(options)` | Remove reaction from comment/message | JWT |

**MCP Tool Equivalents:**
- `gala_launchpad_create_flag`
- `gala_launchpad_list_flags`
- `gala_launchpad_dismiss_flag`
- `gala_launchpad_action_flag`
- `gala_launchpad_fetch_comments`
- `gala_launchpad_post_comment`
- `gala_launchpad_delete_comment`
- `gala_launchpad_add_reaction`
- `gala_launchpad_remove_reaction`

content-reactions.explanation:
## Content Reactions - SDK v5.13.0+

Add and remove reactions on chat messages and pool comments. Reactions provide
social engagement features for community interaction.

**Covers Methods:**
- `addContentReaction()` - Add reaction to any content
- `removeContentReaction()` - Remove reaction from any content
- `addReactionToChatMessage()` - Add reaction specifically to chat message
- `removeReactionFromChatMessage()` - Remove reaction from chat message
- `addReactionToComment()` - Add reaction specifically to pool comment
- `removeReactionFromComment()` - Remove reaction from pool comment

## Adding Reactions

```typescript
import { createLaunchpadSDK } from '@gala-chain/launchpad-sdk';

const sdk = createLaunchpadSDK({
  privateKey: process.env.PRIVATE_KEY,
});

await sdk.login();

// Generic method - works for any content type
await sdk.addContentReaction({
  messageId: 'msg-123',
  reactionType: '👍',
  tokenName: 'mytoken', // optional - backend can resolve from messageId
});

// Specific method for chat messages
await sdk.addReactionToChatMessage({
  tokenName: 'mytoken',
  messageId: 'chat-msg-456',
  reactionType: '🔥',
});

// Specific method for pool comments
await sdk.addReactionToComment({
  tokenName: 'mytoken',
  messageId: 'comment-789',
  reactionType: '❤️',
});
```

## Removing Reactions

```typescript
// Generic method
await sdk.removeContentReaction({
  messageId: 'msg-123',
  reactionType: '👍',
});

// Specific method for chat messages
await sdk.removeReactionFromChatMessage({
  tokenName: 'mytoken',
  messageId: 'chat-msg-456',
  reactionType: '🔥',
});

// Specific method for pool comments
await sdk.removeReactionFromComment({
  tokenName: 'mytoken',
  messageId: 'comment-789',
  reactionType: '❤️',
});
```

## Common Reaction Types

| Emoji | Meaning |
|-------|---------|
| 👍 | Thumbs up / Like |
| ❤️ | Love |
| 🔥 | Fire / Hot |
| 🚀 | Rocket / Moon |
| 😂 | Laughing |

## SDK Methods Reference

| Method | Description | Auth |
|--------|-------------|------|
| `addContentReaction(options)` | Add reaction to any content | JWT |
| `removeContentReaction(options)` | Remove reaction from content | JWT |
| `addReactionToChatMessage(options)` | Add reaction to chat message | JWT |
| `removeReactionFromChatMessage(options)` | Remove reaction from chat message | JWT |
| `addReactionToComment(options)` | Add reaction to pool comment | JWT |
| `removeReactionFromComment(options)` | Remove reaction from pool comment | JWT |

**MCP Tool Equivalents:**
- `gala_launchpad_add_content_reaction`
- `gala_launchpad_remove_content_reaction`
- `gala_launchpad_add_reaction_to_chat_message`
- `gala_launchpad_remove_reaction_from_chat_message`
- `gala_launchpad_add_reaction_to_comment`
- `gala_launchpad_remove_reaction_from_comment`

trade-history.explanation:
## Trade History

Query and analyze trading activity for tokens.

### Basic Usage

```typescript
import { LaunchpadSDK } from '@gala-chain/launchpad-sdk';

const sdk = new LaunchpadSDK({ environment: 'production' });

// Get recent trades for a token
const result = await sdk.getTrades({
  tokenName: 'anime',
  limit: 10,
  page: 1
});

for (const trade of result.trades) {

}
```

### Filter by Trade Type

```typescript
// Get only buy orders
const buyTrades = await sdk.getTrades({
  tokenName: 'anime',
  txnType: 'BUY',
  limit: 50
});

// Get only sell orders
const sellTrades = await sdk.getTrades({
  tokenName: 'anime',
  txnType: 'SELL',
  limit: 50
});
```

### Date Range Queries

```typescript
const oneWeekAgo = new Date(Date.now() - 7 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000);
const now = new Date();

const recentTrades = await sdk.getTrades({
  tokenName: 'anime',
  startDate: oneWeekAgo,
  endDate: now,
  limit: 50
});
```

### Filter by User

```typescript
// Get trades for a specific wallet
const userTrades = await sdk.getTrades({
  tokenName: 'anime',
  userAddress: 'eth|0x1234...',
  limit: 20
});
```

### Pagination

```typescript
// Paginate through all trades using offset-based pagination
let offset = 0;
let hasMore = true;

while (hasMore) {
  const result = await sdk.getTrades({ tokenName: 'anime', offset, limit: 50 });

  hasMore = result.trades.length === 50;
  offset += 50;
}
```

**MCP Tool Equivalents:**
- `gala_launchpad_get_trades`

token-ban-management.explanation:
# Token Ban Management - SDK v6.x.0+

Platform-wide token ban operations for overseers. Banned tokens are hidden from ALL listings
and have actions (comments, streaming, chat) blocked. This is different from user bans which
only affect specific users on specific tokens.

**Access Control:** All methods require either:
- streamAdminApiKey (server-to-server)
- JWT with overseer status (authenticated overseer user)

**Effects of Token Bans:**
- Hidden from ALL pool listings (including creator's profile)
- Comments blocked on banned tokens
- Live streaming blocked on banned tokens
- Chat messages blocked on banned tokens
- Trading NOT blocked (GalaChain handles trading independently)

## Banning a Token

```typescript
import { createLaunchpadSDK } from '@gala-chain/launchpad-sdk';

// Using Admin API key
const sdk = createLaunchpadSDK({
  streamAdminApiKey: process.env.STREAM_ADMIN_API_KEY,
});

// Or using JWT auth (must be an overseer)
const sdkWithAuth = createLaunchpadSDK({
  privateKey: process.env.PRIVATE_KEY,
});
await sdkWithAuth.login({ walletAddress: 'eth|0x...' });

// Ban a token with reason
const result = await sdk.banToken({
  tokenName: 'scamtoken',
  reason: 'Fraudulent project - reported by multiple users',
});

// Ban without reason (optional)
await sdk.banToken({ tokenName: 'problematictoken' });
```

## Unbanning a Token

```typescript
// Remove a token ban
const result = await sdk.unbanToken({ tokenName: 'scamtoken' });

// Token is now:
// - Visible in pool listings again
// - Comments re-enabled
// - Live streaming re-enabled
// - Chat re-enabled
```

## Checking Token Ban Status

```typescript
// Check if a specific token is banned
const status = await sdk.isTokenBanned({ tokenName: 'sometoken' });

if (status.banned) {

} else {

}

// getTokenBan is an alias - use whichever is more readable
const details = await sdk.getTokenBan({ tokenName: 'sometoken' });
```

## Listing All Banned Tokens

```typescript
// Get first page with default limit (20)
const page1 = await sdk.listTokenBans({});

for (const ban of page1.items) {

}

// Search for specific tokens (partial match, case-insensitive)
const searchResults = await sdk.listTokenBans({
  search: 'scam',
  page: 1,
  limit: 10,
});

// Paginate through all banned tokens
let cursor: string | undefined;
let hasMore = true;
while (hasMore) {
  const results = await sdk.listTokenBans({ cursor, limit: 20 });

  for (const ban of results.items) {

  }
  hasMore = results.pageInfo.hasNextPage;
  cursor = results.pageInfo.nextCursor;
}
```

## Important Notes

1. **Permanent Bans Only**: Token bans do not expire. They remain in effect until
   explicitly removed by an overseer.

2. **Case Normalization**: Token names are automatically normalized to lowercase
   in all requests and responses.

3. **Idempotency**: Banning an already-banned token returns a 409 Conflict error.
   Unbanning a non-banned token returns a 404 Not Found error.

4. **Trading Continues**: Token bans do NOT stop trading on GalaChain. The
   launchpad hides visibility and blocks social features only.

**MCP Tool Equivalents:**
- `gala_launchpad_ban_token`
- `gala_launchpad_unban_token`
- `gala_launchpad_list_token_bans`
- `gala_launchpad_get_token_ban`
- `gala_launchpad_is_token_banned`

nft-collection-management.explanation:
# NFT Collection Management - SDK v5.12.0+

Create and manage NFT collections, token classes, and mint NFTs on GalaChain.

**Key Concepts:**
- **Collection**: A named grouping for NFT token classes (claimed for 10,000 GALA)
- **Token Class**: A specific type/rarity within a collection (created for 1,000 GALA)
- **NFT Instance**: Individual NFT minted from a token class (dynamic fee based on quantity)

## Check Collection Availability

```typescript
import { createLaunchpadSDK } from '@gala-chain/launchpad-sdk';

const sdk = createLaunchpadSDK({ privateKey: 'your-private-key' });

// Check if a collection name is available
const available = await sdk.isNftCollectionAvailable('MyEpicNFTs');

// Get fee for claiming a collection
const claimFee = await sdk.getNftCollectionClaimFee();

```

## Claim a Collection

```typescript
// Claim an available collection name
const result = await sdk.claimNftCollection({
  collectionName: 'MyEpicNFTs',
  description: 'Epic NFT collection for gaming.',
});

// Fetch your owned collections
const collections = await sdk.fetchNftCollections(walletAddress);
for (const collection of collections) {

}
```

## Create Token Classes (Rarities)

```typescript
// Get fee for creating a token class
const classCreateFee = await sdk.getNftTokenClassCreateFee();

// Create a token class (rarity tier)
const classResult = await sdk.createNftTokenClass({
  collectionName: 'MyEpicNFTs',
  tokenClassName: 'LegendaryWizard',
  description: 'Ultra-rare legendary wizard NFTs.',
  maximumSupply: '100',  // Max NFTs of this type
  data: {
    rarity: 'legendary',
    class: 'wizard',
    power: '9000',
  },
});

// Fetch token classes for your collection
const classes = await sdk.fetchNftTokenClasses({
  collectionName: 'MyEpicNFTs',
});
for (const tokenClass of classes) {

}
```

## Estimate Mint Fees

```typescript
// Estimate fee for minting multiple NFTs
const mintFeeEstimate = await sdk.estimateNftMintFee({
  collectionName: 'MyEpicNFTs',
  tokenClassName: 'LegendaryWizard',
  quantity: 5,
});

// Estimate multiple operations at once
const bundleFee = await sdk.estimateNftOperationFees({
  operations: [
    { type: 'claim_collection' },
    { type: 'create_token_class', collectionName: 'MyEpicNFTs' },
    { type: 'mint', quantity: 10 },
  ],
});

for (const op of bundleFee.breakdown) {

}
```

## Mint NFTs

```typescript
// Mint NFT instances from a token class
const mintResult = await sdk.mintNft({
  collectionName: 'MyEpicNFTs',
  tokenClassName: 'LegendaryWizard',
  quantity: 5,
  to: 'eth|0x...', // Recipient wallet
  metadata: {
    attributes: [
      { name: 'level', value: '50' },
      { name: 'element', value: 'fire' },
    ],
  },
});

// Check NFT balances
const balances = await sdk.fetchNftBalances(walletAddress);
for (const balance of balances) {

}

// Filter by collection
const collectionBalances = await sdk.fetchNftBalances(walletAddress, 'MyEpicNFTs');
```

## Complete Workflow

```typescript
// 1. Check availability
const available = await sdk.isNftCollectionAvailable('MyEpicNFTs');
if (!available) throw new Error('Collection name taken');

// 2. Claim collection (10,000 GALA)
const claimResult = await sdk.claimNftCollection({
  collectionName: 'MyEpicNFTs',
  description: 'My epic NFT collection.',
});

// 3. Create token class (1,000 GALA)
const classResult = await sdk.createNftTokenClass({
  collectionName: 'MyEpicNFTs',
  tokenClassName: 'Legendary',
  description: 'Legendary tier NFTs.',
  maximumSupply: '1000',
});

// 4. Estimate mint fee
const fee = await sdk.estimateNftMintFee({
  collectionName: 'MyEpicNFTs',
  tokenClassName: 'Legendary',
  quantity: 100,
});

// 5. Mint NFTs
const mintResult = await sdk.mintNft({
  collectionName: 'MyEpicNFTs',
  tokenClassName: 'Legendary',
  quantity: 100,
  to: userWallet,
});

// 6. Verify ownership
const balances = await sdk.fetchNftBalances(userWallet, 'MyEpicNFTs');

```

